# Wheat and Whisper Website Customization Checklist

Use this checklist to personalize your website before or after launch.

## üöÄ Before Launch (Critical)

- [ ] **Deploy to GitHub Pages**
  - Follow DEPLOYMENT-GUIDE.md
  - Verify site is live at your GitHub Pages URL

- [ ] **Update Contact Information** (in `index.html`)
  - [ ] Replace "The Prairie" with your actual location
  - [ ] Add your real email address (replace hello@wheatandwhisper.com)
  - [ ] Add your Instagram handle and link
  - [ ] Add Facebook page link (if applicable)

- [ ] **Test Forms**
  - [ ] Decide on newsletter service (Mailchimp, ConvertKit, etc.)
  - [ ] Set up contact form backend (FormSpree, Netlify Forms, or email service)
  - [ ] Update form actions in `index.html`

## üì∏ Content Updates (High Priority)

- [ ] **Add Real Photos**
  - [ ] Replace all image placeholders with your farm photos
  - [ ] Hero/header area - landscape shots of the farm
  - [ ] About section - candid farm life photos
  - [ ] Gallery - horses, prairie, products, daily life
  - [ ] Compress images before uploading (use tinypng.com)

- [ ] **Customize Text**
  - [ ] About section - tell your unique story
  - [ ] Add details about your horses (names, personalities)
  - [ ] Update product descriptions if you're selling items
  - [ ] Personalize the newsletter signup message

- [ ] **Logo & Branding**
  - [ ] Confirm logo looks good on all pages
  - [ ] Add favicon (small icon in browser tab)
  - [ ] Ensure colors match your brand

## üõçÔ∏è E-Commerce Setup (If Selling Products)

Choose ONE to start:

### Option A: Etsy Shop (Recommended to Start)
- [ ] Set up Etsy shop
- [ ] Add product listings
- [ ] Link shop from your website
- [ ] Update "Shop" section in navigation

### Option B: Shopify Store (Like Slow Sunday)
- [ ] Sign up for Shopify
- [ ] Import products
- [ ] Set up payment processing
- [ ] Connect domain or link from GitHub site

### Option C: Simple Buy Buttons
- [ ] Set up Stripe account
- [ ] Create product pages
- [ ] Add buy button code
- [ ] Test checkout flow

## üé® Design Enhancements (Optional)

- [ ] **Navigation Updates**
  - [ ] Add "Shop" link (if selling)
  - [ ] Add "Blog" section (if starting a blog)
  - [ ] Add "Gallery" page for more photos

- [ ] **New Sections**
  - [ ] "Meet the Horses" - individual horse profiles
  - [ ] "Our Products" - showcase soaps/goods
  - [ ] "Visit Us" - booking form for farm visits
  - [ ] "Blog" - farm stories and updates

- [ ] **Additional Pages**
  - [ ] Create separate pages (copy index.html as template)
  - [ ] Gallery page with more photos
  - [ ] About page with longer story
  - [ ] Products page with catalog

## üîß Technical Improvements (As Needed)

- [ ] **SEO Optimization**
  - [ ] Add meta descriptions to HTML
  - [ ] Include alt text for all images
  - [ ] Submit site to Google Search Console
  - [ ] Create sitemap

- [ ] **Analytics**
  - [ ] Set up Google Analytics
  - [ ] Track visitor behavior
  - [ ] Monitor popular pages

- [ ] **Performance**
  - [ ] Compress images (all should be under 500KB)
  - [ ] Test site speed (use PageSpeed Insights)
  - [ ] Optimize for mobile viewing

- [ ] **Custom Domain** (Optional)
  - [ ] Purchase domain (wheatandwhisper.com?)
  - [ ] Configure DNS settings
  - [ ] Add CNAME file to repository
  - [ ] Update links to use new domain

## üì± Social Media Integration

- [ ] **Connect Accounts**
  - [ ] Link Instagram profile
  - [ ] Link Facebook page
  - [ ] Add social sharing buttons
  - [ ] Consider Instagram feed embed

- [ ] **Content Strategy**
  - [ ] Cross-post website updates to social media
  - [ ] Share behind-the-scenes content
  - [ ] Announce new products/blog posts
  - [ ] Engage with followers

## ‚úçÔ∏è Content Calendar (Ongoing)

- [ ] **Blog Posts** (if adding blog)
  - [ ] Plan 1-2 posts per month
  - [ ] Topics: farm life, horse care, product making
  - [ ] Share personal stories and experiences

- [ ] **Photo Updates**
  - [ ] Seasonal photos (spring flowers, winter snow)
  - [ ] New horses or animals
  - [ ] Product photos as you make new items
  - [ ] Behind-the-scenes process shots

- [ ] **Newsletter**
  - [ ] Plan monthly or bi-monthly sends
  - [ ] Share farm updates
  - [ ] Announce new products
  - [ ] Personal messages to your community

## üìä Growth & Marketing

- [ ] **Expand Reach**
  - [ ] Submit to farm directories
  - [ ] Join local business listings
  - [ ] Network with other farm businesses
  - [ ] Participate in farmers markets (with business cards)

- [ ] **Customer Engagement**
  - [ ] Respond to all contact form submissions
  - [ ] Engage on social media
  - [ ] Share customer testimonials
  - [ ] Build community around your brand

- [ ] **Product Development**
  - [ ] Test new soap scents/products
  - [ ] Gather customer feedback
  - [ ] Create seasonal offerings
  - [ ] Collaborate with other makers

## üéØ Priority Order

**Week 1: Get it Live**
1. Deploy to GitHub Pages
2. Add 3-5 real photos
3. Update contact info
4. Test on mobile phone

**Week 2-3: Polish Content**
5. Replace all placeholder images
6. Rewrite about section with your story
7. Set up newsletter service
8. Connect social media

**Month 2: Add Products**
9. Set up Etsy shop OR product pages
10. Add shop link to navigation
11. Photograph products professionally
12. Launch with announcement

**Ongoing: Grow & Engage**
13. Post regularly on social media
14. Send monthly newsletters
15. Add blog posts when inspired
16. Continuously improve based on feedback

## üí° Tips for Success

1. **Start Simple** - Launch with basics, improve over time
2. **Use Quality Photos** - Natural light, tell a story
3. **Be Authentic** - Share your real farm life
4. **Stay Consistent** - Regular updates build audience
5. **Engage Community** - Respond to all messages
6. **Think Long-term** - Build slowly and sustainably

